data.故事: 曹升和王红是一对夫妻，一日王红做好了晚餐，曹升品尝了一口，说：“我们家是不是好久没买盐了？”
data.问题: 曹升说这句话时，他真正想说的是什么？
data.选项A: A. 曹升在询问家中的盐是否用尽了。
data.选项B: B. 曹升在表达他对盐的需求增大了。
data.选项C: C. 曹升暗示王红做的晚餐盐放得不够。
data.选项D: D. 曹升在提醒他们需要购买更多的食材。
data.STORY: Cao Sheng and Wang Hong are a couple. One day, Wang Hong makes dinner, Cao Sheng takes a bite and says, "Does our home not buy salt for a long time?"
data.QUESTION: What does Cao Sheng really want to say when he says this?
data.OPTION-A: Cao Sheng is asking if the salt in the house is used up.
data.OPTION-B: Cao Sheng is expressing his increased need for salt.
data.OPTION-C: Cao Sheng implies that the dinner Wang Hong makes does not have enough salt.
data.OPTION-D: Cao Sheng is reminding them that they need to buy more ingredients.

data.故事: 章程临近大学毕业，他除了少数专业课的书寄回了家，其他公共科目的书本全部打算装袋子卖了。校园里面收废旧书本的商贩很多，他随便选了一个商贩卖书，一袋子书给商贩称了40斤，五毛一斤 ，商贩给了章程20元，然后就要将书扔在他的车子上。这时章程的朋友陆颖路过，突然说：“自己最近怎么瘦了这么多！”, 然后头也不回的走了。

data.选项C: C. 陆颖暗示章程序时需要保持身材。
data.选项D: D. 陆颖暗示自己最近可能生病了。
data.STORY: Zhang Cheng is about to graduate from university. Besides a few professional books he sends home, he plans to pack and sell all other public subject books. There are many vendors in the campus who buy old books. He randomly chooses a vendor to sell books. A bag of books weighs 40 jin for the vendor, half a yuan per jin, the vendor gives Zhang Cheng 20 yuan, and then he wants to throw the books on his car. At this time, Zhang Cheng's friend Lu Ying passes by and suddenly says, "How do I lose so much weight recently!", and then he walks away without looking back.
data.QUESTION: What does Lu Ying really mean when he says this sentence?
data.OPTION-A: Lu Ying implies that he is losing weight recently.
data.OPTION-B: Lu Ying implies that the vendor's scale might be tampered with.
data.OPTION-C: Lu Ying implies that Zhang Cheng needs to keep his figure at all times.
data.OPTION-D: Lu Ying implies that he might be sick recently.

data.OPTION-D: The staff is suggesting that Hongjie find a suitable signing tool.

One day, he picks up a female passenger, who turns out to be his ex-girlfriend. Along the way, the two are silent, the ex-girlfriend's expression struggles, as if she is making some mental preparation. After arriving at the destination, she quietly asks Wang Yuan: "Can we go back?"
data.QUESTION: When the current girlfriend says this sentence, what does she really want to say?
data.OPTION-A: She wants to ask Wang Yuan if he can take her home
data.OPTION-B: She asks Wang Yuan if the two can be boyfriend and girlfriend again
data.OPTION-C: She is getting Wang Yuan's opinion on running Didi as a career choice
data.OPTION-D: She implies that she takes the wrong car, asking Wang Yuan if he can take her back to the place where she hails the taxi

data.选项D: D. 他表明自己拒绝前女友复合的请求。

data.STORY: Chen Wei rides an electric bike to the market to buy fruits. He passes by a fruit stall, just stops the bike, turns his head on the bike to ask the boss, "How much is the orange per pound?" The boss replies, "Hold your phone well, come down and see."

data.OPTION-A: The boss hopes that Chen Wei gets off the car safely to avoid falling.
data.OPTION-B: The boss hopes that Chen Wei checks the current market price of oranges with his phone.
data.OPTION-C: The boss hints that there are phone thieves around.
data.OPTION-D: The boss suggests that Chen Wei personally selects and checks the quality of the oranges.

data.故事:
一个理科男生每晚都去一个教室自习，每次都坐在一个不认识的女生后面。渐渐地，男生喜欢上了女生，但一直没有勇气表白。舍友们知道后，全都鼓励他。一天晚上，男生终于鼓足了勇气，写了一封表白信，递到女生的手里。
女生看了一会儿之后，收拾学习用具，转身对男生说：我想回去了，你呢？
data.问题: 当女生说出这句话时，她真正想说的是什么？
data.选项A: A. 她表明自己要回家了，询问男生是否也要回家。
data.选项B: B. 她希望男生可以明白她需要独处。
data.选项C: C. 她不想和男生在一起。
data.选项D: D. 她暗示自己同意了男生的表白。
data.STORY: A science male student goes to a classroom to study every night, always sitting behind a girl he does not know. Gradually, the boy falls in love with the girl, but he never has the courage to confess. When his roommates know, they all encourage him. One night, the boy finally gathers the courage, writes a love letter, and gives it to the girl.\nThe girl looks at it for a while, packs up her study tools, turns around and says to the boy: I want to go back, what about you?
data.QUESTION: What does she really want to say when the girl says this sentence?
data.OPTION-A: She indicates that she wants to go home and asks if the boy also wants to go home.
data.OPTION-B: She hopes the boy understands that she needs to be alone.
data.OPTION-C: She does not want to be with the boy.
data.OPTION-D: She implies that she agrees with the boy's confession.

data.选项C: C. 她暗示舞蹈服已经旧了，需要购买新的。
data.选项D: D. 她对舞蹈社团的成员们抱怨太多。
data.STORY: Xiao Yang is the person in charge of the dance club. One day, she looks at the club's dance costumes and says, "These dance costumes make people feel heartbroken."

data.OPTION-A: She thinks the color of the dance costumes is not good.
data.OPTION-B: She believes someone secretly wears the club's dance costumes.
data.OPTION-C: She implies that the dance costumes are old and need to buy new ones.
data.OPTION-D: She complains too much about the members of the dance club.

data.故事: 小杨所在的公司周三有周例会。某周一，领导带着小王去会见客户张局，两人一直相谈甚欢，但谈的都是一些无关痛痒的话题，因为正事存在观点分歧。眼看着将近饭点，出现了下面几句对话： 领导：“张局，快到饭点了，看您有时间吗？想约您吃个饭？” 然后领导转过身，边眨眼睛，边对小杨说：“小杨，咱们晚上单位还有会议吗？”
data.问题: 当领导问小杨这个问题的时候，他的目的是什么？
data.选项A: A. 领导想向小杨询问会议时间，以安排和客户的饭局。
data.选项B: B. 领导希望小杨回答今晚有会议，以此借口结束会面。
data.选项C: C.领导想了解小杨对周例会的准备情况。
data.选项D: D. 领导希望询问小杨愿不愿不参加会议，而陪他们吃饭。
data.STORY: Xiao Yang's company holds a weekly meeting every Wednesday. On a certain Monday, the leader takes Xiao Wang to meet with client Director Zhang. The two of them chat happily, but they only talk about some irrelevant topics because there are disagreements on the main issues. As it approaches mealtime, the following conversation occurs: Leader: "Director Zhang, it is almost mealtime, do you have time? I want to invite you to have a meal." Then the leader turns around, winks, and says to Xiao Yang: "Xiao Yang, do we have a meeting at the unit tonight?"
data.QUESTION: What is the leader's purpose when he asks Xiao Yang this question?
data.OPTION-A: The leader wants to ask Xiao Yang about the meeting time to arrange a meal with the client.
data.OPTION-B: The leader hopes Xiao Yang answers that there is a meeting tonight, so he can use this as an excuse to end the meeting.
data.OPTION-C: The leader wants to understand Xiao Yang's preparation for the weekly meeting.
data.OPTION-D: The leader wants to ask if Xiao Yang is willing to skip the meeting and join them for dinner.

data.故事: 小汪和网络上认识的女生小兰的见面约在了酒店。在前台，小兰不愿意出示身份证登记。 前台工作人员问：“您是一位还是两位？两位的话需要出示双方身份证的先生。” 小汪回头看着小兰，她慢慢走到沙发边上坐下仍然没有出示身份证的意思。于是小汪转过头问：“两位，那怎么办？” 此时前台工作人员又问：“您是一位入住还是两位呢？”
data.问题: 当工作人员提出这个问题的时候，他的目的是什么？
data.选项A: A. 他没有听清楚小汪之前的回答，要再进行确认。
data.选项B: B. 他正在重新核实小汪的住宿需求。
data.选项C: C. 他暗示小汪可回答一位入住，这样只需要用一个人的身份证。
data.选项D: D. 他暗示不出示两人身份证就不可以一起住宿。
data.STORY: Xiao Wang and the girl he meets online, Xiao Lan, arrange to meet at a hotel. At the front desk, Xiao Lan does not want to show her ID for registration. The front desk staff asks, "Are you one or two? If two, the gentleman needs to show both IDs." Xiao Wang turns his head and looks at Xiao Lan, she slowly walks to the edge of the sofa and sits down, still showing no intention of showing her ID. So Xiao Wang turns his head and asks, "Two, what to do?" At this time, the front desk staff asks again, "Are you checking in for one or two?"
data.QUESTION: What is his purpose when the staff asks this question?
data.OPTION-A: He does not hear Xiao Wang's previous answer clearly and needs to confirm again.
data.OPTION-B: He is re-verifying Xiao Wang's accommodation needs.
data.OPTION-C: He hints that Xiao Wang can answer one person checks in, so only one person's ID is needed.
data.OPTION-D: He hints that if they do not show both IDs, they cannot stay together.

data.故事: 健身教练张佳丽有一次开车没带安全带被交警拍到了。交警走过来问张佳丽：“为什么没系安全带？是不是怀孕了？”
data.问题: 当交警问这个问题时，他真正的意图是什么？
data.选项A: A. 交警想要了解张佳丽的个人生活
data.选项B: B. 交警想确认张佳丽是否怀孕了，因为怀孕的人不用系安全带
data.选项C: C. 交警希望张佳丽去医院做孕检
data.选项D: D. 交警暗示张佳丽可以回答自己怀孕了，以避免罚款
data.STORY: Fitness coach Zhang Jiali drives without a seatbelt one time and a traffic cop catches her. The traffic cop comes over and asks Zhang Jiali, "Why don't you wear a seatbelt? Are you pregnant?"
data.QUESTION: What is the real intention of the traffic cop when he asks this question?
data.OPTION-A: The traffic cop wants to know about Zhang Jiali's personal life
data.OPTION-B: The traffic cop wants to confirm if Zhang Jiali is pregnant, because pregnant people do not need to wear seatbelts
data.OPTION-C: The traffic cop hopes Zhang Jiali goes to the hospital for a pregnancy test
data.OPTION-D: The traffic cop implies that Zhang Jiali can say she is pregnant to avoid a fine

data.STORY: One day, Xiao Ming passes by a small alley, there is a small stall at the entrance of the alley that sells fried goods. Because Xiao Ming likes to eat melon seeds very much, he steps forward to buy two pounds. When buying, Xiao Ming gives the boss a hundred yuan bill, the boss takes the money, lowers his head and mutters a few words with the boss lady, and then hands out the previous bill, saying, "I can't make change, no small change." Xiao Ming feels a bit strange, but doesn't think much about it, takes the money and is about to walk away, Zhang San, who is passing by, says to himself, "Your melon seeds, they don't look like the real thing." After saying this, Zhang San walks away, and the boss just lowers his head and says nothing.

data.故事: 一位先生爱慕一位女士，买了一条贵重的项链送给她，这位女士微笑着说：“这条项链真漂亮，前阵子我男朋友也买了一条送我，想不到你们有一样的品味。”
data.问题: 当这位女士说这句话的时候，她真正想说的是什么？
data.选项A: A. 女士想表达出她对这条项链的喜欢。
data.选项B: B. 女士在暗示她并不喜欢这种款式的项链。
data.选项C: C. 女士暗示她已有男朋友。
data.选项D: D. 女士在赞美这位男士的品味。
data.STORY: A gentleman admires a lady and buys her an expensive necklace. The lady smiles and says, "This necklace is really beautiful. A while ago, my boyfriend also buys one for me. I don't expect you guys to have the same taste."
data.QUESTION: What does she really want to say when this lady says this?
data.OPTION-A: The lady wants to express her liking for this necklace.
data.OPTION-B: The lady hints that she does not like this style of necklace.
data.OPTION-C: The lady hints that she already has a boyfriend.
data.OPTION-D: The lady praises the taste of this gentleman.

output:
[推理过程]
（1）女士说这句话时，她的男朋友还给她送了一条项链，这意味着她在说这句话时，她的男朋友还在。因此，她不可能真正想说她已经有了男朋友（C选项）。

（2）女士还提到了说前阵子她的男朋友送她的是同款项链，这意味着她有意向两位新交际者表现出她们送给她的项链是来的不止是他。使送礼者产生错误的假设。

（3）结合上面的分析，当女士说这句话“想不到你们有一样的品味”的真正意图，并不是表达她对这条项链的喜欢（A选项），赞美这位送礼者的品味（D选项），也不点暗示她不喜欢这种款式的项链（B选项），而是为了避免使送礼者知道她的男朋友已经送给她同款项链，故意用“ frente differentiations” 的方式嘲弄了这三个来福袋送礼者的品味。

data.故事:
鸿杰去银行帮朋友办事，朋友在外地，他找到工作人员要来了办事需要填写的表单，看到了签名那栏，愣住了，因为显示要本人签字。
他很耿直的问工作人员：“我朋友在外地，我可以代签吗？”
工作人员说：“这里有监控，是没法别人代签的，出去找本人签。”
他很着急的说：“我朋友真的回不来，行个方便吧。”
工作人员还是那句话：“这里有监控，别人没法代签，出去找本人签。”
data.问题: 当工作人员说这句话时，他真正想说的是什么？
data.选项A: A. 工作人员是在硬性要求鸿杰必须找他的朋友来银行签字。
data.选项B: B. 工作人员在暗示鸿杰可以走出银行后帮朋友代签。
data.选项C: C. 工作人员是再次确认了规定，即银行内不允许他人代签。
data.选项D: D. 工作人员是在建议鸿杰去找合适的签字工具。
data.STORY:
Hongjie goes to the bank to help a friend with some business. His friend is out of town. He gets the form that needs to be filled out from the staff and stops when he sees the signature column because it requires the person's own signature.
He asks the staff very straightforwardly: "My friend is out of town, can I sign for him?"
The staff says: "There is surveillance here, it is impossible for others to sign on behalf, go find the person to sign."
He says anxiously: "My friend really can't come back, please make it convenient."
The staff still says: "There is surveillance here, others can't sign on behalf, go find the person to sign."
data.QUESTION: What does the staff really mean when he says this?
data.OPTION-A: The staff is insisting that Hongjie must find his friend to come to the bank to sign.
data.OPTION-B: The staff is hinting that Hongjie can sign for his friend after leaving the bank.
data.OPTION-C: The staff is reconfirming the rule that the bank does not allow others to sign on behalf.
data.OPTION-D: The staff is suggesting that Hongjie find a suitable signing tool.

Xiao Wang turns his head and looks at Xiao Lan, she slowly walks to the edge of the sofa and sits down, still showing no intention of showing her ID. [思维过程]

Rebecca说“我喜欢动物，尤其是狗。”，这个意思可以由多种解读，各自对应的答案选项。但是，因为这个句子对于一个即将过生日的人来说是一个非常合理的话题。

如果 Rebecca 说的是“我喜欢了解动物，特别是狗的行为习性”，她自然可以从“我喜欢动物，特别是狗。”这个句子转移到A选项。但是，直接之后她的“尤其是狗”，没有表明她是对他们生活习性产生兴趣的。

如果 Rebecca 说的是“我期待父亲让为我购买一只狗作为生日礼物”，她的语言显然会从“尤其是狗”这个句子衔接到B选项。因为“尤其是狗”极大可能性是她自己希望满足生日愿望的暗示。

Episode Rocket Rise外另一个可能性是“我期待能够去动物园参观，动物以狗为主”(C选项)。但是这个解读从语法上与rebecca说的话不匹配。

最后一个可能性的话，rebecca可以从一开始的话题“我喜欢狗”衔接到显然是让父母带她去见狗D选项。

data.故事: 明凯在大学爬泰山的时候买了个钥匙扣。他参加工作后，他的领导偶然看到这个钥匙扣，说“你这钥匙扣真漂亮啊，哪里买的？”明凯便把自己在泰山的经历绘声绘色说了一遍。过了几天，领导又看到明凯的钥匙扣，好像失忆了一样，又问“你这钥匙扣真漂亮啊，哪里买的？“
data.问题: 领导说这句话的时候，真正的意图是什么？
data.选项A: A. 领导对明凯的钥匙扣很感兴趣，考虑自己也去买一个。

data.选项C: C. 领导想检验明凯的耐心，探究他是否愿意反复解释同一件事。
data.选项D: D. 领导提醒小明这个钥匙扣使他分心了
data.STORY: Mingkai buys a keychain when he climbs Mount Tai in college. data.OPTION-C: The leader wants to test Mingkai's patience, to explore whether he is willing to explain the same thing repeatedly.
data.OPTION-D: The leader reminds Mingkai that this keychain distracts him.

data.故事: 小红大概晚上9点到达火车站候车厅，进入后，她询问乘务员“这里可以待多久？”。乘务员回答：“最多三个小时，也就是到12点，你要不要现在就进去？”小红说：“可以的，我是凌晨3点的火车，我想着在这里休息到12点，出去再呆2个多小时。”此时，然后乘务员突然提醒说：“注意听广播提醒你上列车，不要误车。”
data.问题: 乘务员说这句话的时候，真正的意思是什么？
data.选项A: A. 乘务员在暗示小红可以在候车厅一直休息，直到上车。
data.选项B: B. 乘务员在告诫小红，夜晚出行安全问题需要提高警惕。
data.选项C: C. 乘务员在告诉小红，她必须在12点之前离开候车厅。
data.选项D: D. 乘务员在提醒小红要关注列车时刻表，以防错过火车。

The conductor replies, "Up to three hours, which is until 12 o'clock, do you want to go in now?" Xiao Hong says, "Yes, I am on the 3 am train, I think about resting here until 12 o'clock, then go out and stay for more than 2 hours." At this time, the conductor suddenly reminds, "Pay attention to the broadcast to remind you to get on the train, do not miss the train."
data.QUESTION: What is the real meaning when the conductor says this?

data.OPTION-B: The conductor warns Xiao Hong that she needs to be vigilant about safety issues when traveling at night.
data.OPTION-C: The conductor tells Xiao Hong that she must leave the waiting room before 12 o'clock.
data.OPTION-D: The conductor reminds Xiao Hong to pay attention to the train schedule to prevent missing the train.

data.故事: 小刘总喜欢将没做完的工作委托给同事小张帮忙完成，一日，小刘在请求小张帮忙时，小张说：“我不喜欢麻烦别人”。
data.问题: 小张说这句话时，他真正想说的是什么？
data.选项A: A. 小张认为自己很有能力，不需要别人帮忙。
data.选项B: B. 小张不希望小刘再来麻烦他。
data.选项C: C. 小张希望小刘今后能提升自己的工作能力。
data.选项D: D. 小张想表达他对帮助别人很有热情。
data.STORY: Xiao Liu always likes to delegate unfinished work to his colleague Xiao Zhang to help complete. One day, when Xiao Liu asks Xiao Zhang for help, Xiao Zhang says, "I do not like to bother others."

data.OPTION-B: Xiao Zhang does not want Xiao Liu to bother him anymore.
data.OPTION-C: Xiao Zhang hopes that Xiao Liu can improve his work ability in the future.
data.OPTION-D: Xiao Zhang wants to express his enthusiasm for helping others.

data.故事: 刚刚入职的小王和老科长一起在疫情管控点站岗，站岗任务不繁重，但老科长站半天感觉很累。不巧的是管控点设备简陋，只有一个凳子。老科长对小王说“小王同志，你也站半天了，就一个凳子，你坐一会儿吧”

The guard duty is not heavy, but the old section chief feels very tired after standing for half a day. Unfortunately, the equipment at the control point is simple, there is only one stool. data.OPTION-D: The old section chief hopes to initiate a conversation about the condition of the work equipment.

data.故事: 刘伟是一个身材魁梧的肌肉男，某天他第一次去岳父家，吃完了一碗米饭后，给大家讲了个故事：“前几天我到山里去，见到一只大老虎，那虎爪啊……”将空碗往桌上一倒扣，“有这么大！” 岳父立即想到是刘伟还没吃饱，就默默转身进厨房准备给他添饭。结果到了厨房一看，已经没有饭了。岳父略一思索就抱着锅出来，把空锅往桌上一倒扣：“那老虎头是不是有这么大？”
data.问题: 岳父说这句话时，真正想说的意思是什么？
data.选项A: A. 岳父暗示他曾经亲见过一只大老虎
data.选项B: B. 岳父想提醒刘伟不要吹嘘自己的勇气
data.选项C: C. 岳父暗示锅中已经没有饭了
data.选项D: D. 岳父在揶揄刘伟的吃相
data.STORY: Liu Wei is a muscular man with a robust figure. One day, he goes to his father-in-law's house for the first time. After finishing a bowl of rice, he tells everyone a story: "A few days ago, I go to the mountain and see a big tiger, its claws..." He turns the empty bowl upside down on the table, "are this big!" The father-in-law immediately thinks that Liu Wei is still hungry, so he silently turns around and goes into the kitchen to get him more rice. But when he gets to the kitchen, there is no rice left. After a brief thought, the father-in-law comes out with the pot, turns the empty pot upside down on the table: "Is the tiger's head this big?"
data.QUESTION: What does the father-in-law really mean when he says this?
data.OPTION-A: The father-in-law hints that he once sees a big tiger
data.OPTION-B: The father-in-law wants to remind Liu Wei not to boast about his courage
data.OPTION-C: The father-in-law hints that there is no rice left in the pot
data.OPTION-D: The father-in-law is teasing Liu Wei's eating manners

data.OPTION-D: Xiao Wang notices this person's smoking habit.

鸿杰去银行帮朋友办事，朋友在外地，他找到工作人员要来了办事需要填写的表单，看到了签名那栏，愣住了，因为显示要本人签字。
他很耿直的问工作人员：“我朋友在外地，我可以代签吗？”
工作人员说：“这里有监控，是没法别人代签的，出去找本人签。”
他很着急的说：“我朋友真的回不来，行个方便吧。”
工作人员还是那句话：“这里有监控，别人没法代签，出去找本人签。”
data.问题: 当工作人员说这句话时，他真正想说的是什么？

data.选项B: B. 工作人员在暗示鸿杰可以走出银行后帮朋友代签。
data.选项C: C. 工作人员是再次确认了规定，即银行内不允许他人代签。
data.选项D: D. 工作人员是在建议鸿杰去找合适的签字工具。
data.STORY:
Hongjie goes to the bank to help a friend with some business. His friend is out of town. He gets the form that needs to be filled out from the staff and stops when he sees the signature column because it requires the person's own signature.
He asks the staff very straightforwardly: "My friend is out of town, can I sign for him?"
The staff says: "There is surveillance here, it is impossible for others to sign on behalf, go find the person to sign."
He says anxiously: "My friend really can't come back, please make it convenient."
The staff still says: "There is surveillance here, others can't sign on behalf, go find the person to sign."
data.QUESTION: What does the staff really mean when he says this?
data.OPTION-A: The staff is insisting that Hongjie must find his friend to come to the bank to sign.
data.OPTION-B: The staff is hinting that Hongjie can sign for his friend after leaving the bank.
data.OPTION-C: The staff is reconfirming the rule that the bank does not allow others to sign on behalf.
data.OPTION-D: The staff is suggesting that Hongjie find a suitable signing tool.

data.STORY: Linda holds her pet dog and enters the house on a winter night, she says to her husband Bob: "Ah, the dog's fur is almost freezing."
data.QUESTION: What does Linda really mean when she says this?
data.OPTION-A: Linda implies to Bob that they should raise the temperature inside the house.
data.OPTION-B: Linda implies to Bob that the pet dog's fur needs cleaning.

data.故事: 高三那会儿，李晨早上经常迟到，连续几天都迟到。班主任生气了，把李晨堵在走廊一通教育，然后拉着李晨去了办公室，对他说：“你这么喜欢睡，那你就在这里安安心心地睡觉吧！今天的课也不要上了！” 然后摔门而出。
data.问题: 当班主任说这句话时，他真正想说的是什么？
data.选项A: A. 班主任希望李晨可以单独在办公室上课
data.选项B: B. 班主任鼓励李晨放弃学业，好好休息
data.选项C: C. 班主任暗示李晨要按时上课，不要迟到
data.选项D: D. 班主任对李晨失望，不希望他再来上课
data.STORY: During the senior year, Li Chen often arrives late in the morning, and he is late for several days in a row. The head teacher gets angry, blocks Li Chen in the corridor for a lecture, then takes Li Chen to the office, and says to him: "You like to sleep so much, then you sleep here peacefully! You do not attend today's class!" Then he slams the door and leaves.
data.QUESTION: What does the head teacher really mean when he says this?
data.OPTION-A: The head teacher hopes that Li Chen can attend class alone in the office
data.OPTION-B: The head teacher encourages Li Chen to give up his studies and rest well
data.OPTION-C: The head teacher implies that Li Chen should attend class on time and not be late
data.OPTION-D: The head teacher is disappointed in Li Chen and does not want him to attend class anymore

data.故事:
一个理科男生每晚都去一个教室自习，每次都坐在一个不认识的女生后面。渐渐地，男生喜欢上了女生，但一直没有勇气表白。舍友们知道后，全都鼓励他。一天晚上，男生终于鼓足了勇气，写了一封表白信，递到女生的手里。
女生看了一会儿之后，收拾学习用具，转身对男生说：我想回去了，你呢？
data.问题: 当女生说出这句话时，她真正想说的是什么？
data.选项A: A. 她表明自己要回家了，询问男生是否也要回家。
data.选项B: B. 她希望男生可以明白她需要独处。
data.选项C: C. 她不想和男生在一起。
data.选项D: D. 她暗示自己同意了男生的表白。
data.STORY: A science male student goes to a classroom to study every night, always sitting behind a girl he does not know. Gradually, the boy falls in love with the girl, but he never has the courage to confess. When his roommates know, they all encourage him. One night, the boy finally gathers the courage, writes a love letter, and gives it to the girl.\nThe girl looks at it for a while, packs up her study tools, turns around and says to the boy: I want to go back, what about you?
data.QUESTION: What does she really want to say when the girl says this sentence?
data.OPTION-A: She indicates that she wants to go home and asks if the boy also wants to go home.
data.OPTION-B: She hopes the boy understands that she needs to be alone.
data.OPTION-C: She does not want to be with the boy.
data.OPTION-D: She implies that she agrees with the boy's confession.

output:
[推理过程]
假设当女生“想回去了，你呢？”这一句信时，她只是简单说的话，还就是她打算离开教室，回家的提议。
答案选项C、D不可成立，因为她的表述完全没有暗示任何不想与此人交往行为。
事实上看到她的两个表述，表意只有说自己打算离去，并不给人感觉她在表明同意男生的表白。
答案选项B。

data.故事: 小杨所在的公司周三有周例会。某周一，领导带着小王去会见客户张局，两人一直相谈甚欢，但谈的都是一些无关痛痒的话题，因为正事存在观点分歧。眼看着将近饭点，出现了下面几句对话： 领导：“张局，快到饭点了，看您有时间吗？想约您吃个饭？” 然后领导转过身，边眨眼睛，边对小杨说：“小杨，咱们晚上单位还有会议吗？”

data.选项C: C.领导想了解小杨对周例会的准备情况。
data.选项D: D. 领导希望询问小杨愿不愿不参加会议，而陪他们吃饭。

data.故事: 某天小明路过一条小巷，巷口有家小摊在卖炒货。因为小明很喜欢吃瓜子，就上前购买了两斤，在购买时小明递给老板一张百元大钞，老板接过钱，低头和老板娘嘀咕几句，又把前一张钞票递了出来，说：“找不开，没零钱。”小明感到有些奇怪，但也没多想，接过钱正想走开，旁边路过的张三自言自语般地说了一句“你这瓜子，不像真货啊。” 说完张三就走了，老板只勾着头不吭声。

data.STORY: One day, Xiao Ming passes by a small alley, there is a small stall at the entrance of the alley that sells fried goods. Because Xiao Ming likes to eat melon seeds very much, he steps forward to buy two pounds. When buying, Xiao Ming gives the boss a hundred yuan bill, the boss takes the money, lowers his head and mutters a few words with the boss lady, and then hands out the previous bill, saying, "I can't make change, no small change." Xiao Ming feels a bit strange, but doesn't think much about it, takes the money and is about to walk away, Zhang San, who is passing by, says to himself, "Your melon seeds, they don't look like the real thing." After saying this, Zhang San walks away, and the boss just lowers his head and says nothing.

data.OPTION-A: Zhang San is hinting that the boss changes Xiao Ming's real money into counterfeit money.

data.故事: 小李在参加驾驶员路考时较为紧张，一进入车内就想要启动发动机。考官在旁边询问，“你准备好了吗！” 小李说：“准备好了！” 考官把自己的安全带拆开又系上，又问了小李一次“你准备好了吗？”
data.问题: 考官说这句话的时候，真正的意思是什么？
data.选项A: A. 考官在询问小李是否有考试压力。
data.选项B: B. 考官正在确认小李是否真的准备好开始测试。
data.选项C: C. 考官在提醒小李系好安全带后再启动发动机。
data.选项D: D. 考官在测试小李对重复问题的耐心。
data.STORY: Xiao Li is quite nervous when participating in the driver's road test, and wants to start the engine as soon as he gets in the car. The examiner asks next to him, "Are you ready!" Xiao Li says, "I am ready!" The examiner unbuckles his seat belt and buckles it again, and asks Xiao Li again, "Are you ready?"
data.QUESTION: What is the real meaning when the examiner says this?
data.OPTION-A: The examiner is asking if Xiao Li is under exam pressure.
data.OPTION-B: The examiner is confirming whether Xiao Li is really ready to start the test.
data.OPTION-C: The examiner is reminding Xiao Li to buckle up the seat belt before starting the engine.
data.OPTION-D: The examiner is testing Xiao Li's patience with repeated questions.

output:
[推理]
考官的行为是把自己的安全带拆开，又系上，显然是检查安全带是否系住并不宽松的。因此，考官此时只是想确认确认小李是否真正在使劲把安全带系紧看似准备好测试，但实际混淆了自己的担心作为提高的小李起始紧张状态。
根据这种推理，小李在考官询问“确认了，你准备好了吗？”的行为似乎是在把安全带系好，不在测量耐心。

data.QUESTION: What is the real intention of the old section chief when he says this?
data.OPTION-A: The old section chief hopes Xiao Wang gives him the stool to sit.

data.故事: 最近小华从外国回来参加了一场宴会，在餐桌上，主办方自带了许多茅台酒。开场后不久，小华的朋友，品酒经验丰富的小张喝了一口桌上的茅台酒，说了一句：“茅台就是不一样啊，味道好。”，随后找了个借口换喝了红酒。
data.问题: 小张说这句话时，他真正想说的意思是什么？
data.选项A: A. 小张喜欢喝红酒，不喜欢茅台酒
data.选项B: B. 小张认为茅台酒的品质优于红酒
data.选项C: C. 小张暗示主办方的茅台酒可能不是真的
data.选项D: D. 小张认为这个宴会的酒品种应该更多样
data.STORY: Recently, Xiaohua comes back from abroad and attends a banquet. At the table, the host brings a lot of Maotai liquor. Not long after the start, Xiaohua's friend, the experienced wine taster Xiaozhang, takes a sip of the Maotai on the table and says, "Maotai is different, it tastes good.", then finds an excuse to switch to red wine.
data.QUESTION: What does Xiaozhang really mean when he says this?
data.OPTION-A: Xiaozhang likes to drink red wine, not Maotai
data.OPTION-B: Xiaozhang thinks the quality of Maotai is better than red wine
data.OPTION-C: Xiaozhang hints that the host's Maotai may not be real
data.OPTION-D: Xiaozhang thinks the variety of wines at this banquet should be more diverse

data.故事: 章程临近大学毕业，他除了少数专业课的书寄回了家，其他公共科目的书本全部打算装袋子卖了。校园里面收废旧书本的商贩很多，他随便选了一个商贩卖书，一袋子书给商贩称了40斤，五毛一斤 ，商贩给了章程20元，然后就要将书扔在他的车子上。这时章程的朋友陆颖路过，突然说：“自己最近怎么瘦了这么多！”, 然后头也不回的走了。
data.问题: 陆颖说这句话时，真正想说的意思是什么？

data.选项D: D. 陆颖暗示自己最近可能生病了。
data.STORY: Zhang Cheng is about to graduate from university. Besides a few professional books he sends home, he plans to pack and sell all other public subject books. There are many vendors in the campus who buy old books. He randomly chooses a vendor to sell books. A bag of books weighs 40 jin for the vendor, half a yuan per jin, the vendor gives Zhang Cheng 20 yuan, and then he wants to throw the books on his car. At this time, Zhang Cheng's friend Lu Ying passes by and suddenly says, "How do I lose so much weight recently!", and then he walks away without looking back.
data.QUESTION: What does Lu Ying really mean when he says this sentence?
data.OPTION-A: Lu Ying implies that he is losing weight recently.
data.OPTION-B: Lu Ying implies that the vendor's scale might be tampered with.
data.OPTION-C: Lu Ying implies that Zhang Cheng needs to keep his figure at all times.
data.OPTION-D: Lu Ying implies that he might be sick recently.

data.STORY: Chen Wei is a college student in Guangdong. data.故事:
鸿杰去银行帮朋友办事，朋友在外地，他找到工作人员要来了办事需要填写的表单，看到了签名那栏，愣住了，因为显示要本人签字。
他很耿直的问工作人员：“我朋友在外地，我可以代签吗？”
工作人员说：“这里有监控，是没法别人代签的，出去找本人签。”
他很着急的说：“我朋友真的回不来，行个方便吧。”
工作人员还是那句话：“这里有监控，别人没法代签，出去找本人签。”
data.问题: 当工作人员说这句话时，他真正想说的是什么？
data.选项A: A. 工作人员是在硬性要求鸿杰必须找他的朋友来银行签字。
data.选项B: B. 工作人员在暗示鸿杰可以走出银行后帮朋友代签。
data.选项C: C. 工作人员是再次确认了规定，即银行内不允许他人代签。
data.选项D: D. 工作人员是在建议鸿杰去找合适的签字工具。
data.STORY:
Hongjie goes to the bank to help a friend with some business. His friend is out of town. He gets the form that needs to be filled out from the staff and stops when he sees the signature column because it requires the person's own signature.
He asks the staff very straightforwardly: "My friend is out of town, can I sign for him?"
The staff says: "There is surveillance here, it is impossible for others to sign on behalf, go find the person to sign."
He says anxiously: "My friend really can't come back, please make it convenient."
The staff still says: "There is surveillance here, others can't sign on behalf, go find the person to sign."
data.QUESTION: What does the staff really mean when he says this?
data.OPTION-A: The staff is insisting that Hongjie must find his friend to come to the bank to sign.
data.OPTION-B: The staff is hinting that Hongjie can sign for his friend after leaving the bank.
data.OPTION-C: The staff is reconfirming the rule that the bank does not allow others to sign on behalf.
data.OPTION-D: The staff is suggesting that Hongjie find a suitable signing tool.

data.故事: 高三那会儿，李晨早上经常迟到，连续几天都迟到。班主任生气了，把李晨堵在走廊一通教育，然后拉着李晨去了办公室，对他说：“你这么喜欢睡，那你就在这里安安心心地睡觉吧！今天的课也不要上了！” 然后摔门而出。
data.问题: 当班主任说这句话时，他真正想说的是什么？
data.选项A: A. 班主任希望李晨可以单独在办公室上课
data.选项B: B. 班主任鼓励李晨放弃学业，好好休息
data.选项C: C. 班主任暗示李晨要按时上课，不要迟到
data.选项D: D. 班主任对李晨失望，不希望他再来上课
data.STORY: During the senior year, Li Chen often arrives late in the morning, and he is late for several days in a row. The head teacher gets angry, blocks Li Chen in the corridor for a lecture, then takes Li Chen to the office, and says to him: "You like to sleep so much, then you sleep here peacefully! You do not attend today's class!" Then he slams the door and leaves.
data.QUESTION: What does the head teacher really mean when he says this?
data.OPTION-A: The head teacher hopes that Li Chen can attend class alone in the office
data.OPTION-B: The head teacher encourages Li Chen to give up his studies and rest well
data.OPTION-C: The head teacher implies that Li Chen should attend class on time and not be late
data.OPTION-D: The head teacher is disappointed in Li Chen and does not want him to attend class anymore

data.故事:
一个理科男生每晚都去一个教室自习，每次都坐在一个不认识的女生后面。渐渐地，男生喜欢上了女生，但一直没有勇气表白。舍友们知道后，全都鼓励他。一天晚上，男生终于鼓足了勇气，写了一封表白信，递到女生的手里。
女生看了一会儿之后，收拾学习用具，转身对男生说：我想回去了，你呢？
data.问题: 当女生说出这句话时，她真正想说的是什么？
data.选项A: A. 她表明自己要回家了，询问男生是否也要回家。
data.选项B: B. 她希望男生可以明白她需要独处。
data.选项C: C. 她不想和男生在一起。
data.选项D: D. 她暗示自己同意了男生的表白。
data.STORY: A science male student goes to a classroom to study every night, always sitting behind a girl he does not know. Gradually, the boy falls in love with the girl, but he never has the courage to confess. When his roommates know, they all encourage him. One night, the boy finally gathers the courage, writes a love letter, and gives it to the girl.\nThe girl looks at it for a while, packs up her study tools, turns around and says to the boy: I want to go back, what about you?
data.QUESTION: What does she really want to say when the girl says this sentence?
data.OPTION-A: She indicates that she wants to go home and asks if the boy also wants to go home.
data.OPTION-B: She hopes the boy understands that she needs to be alone.
data.OPTION-C: She does not want to be with the boy.
data.OPTION-D: She implies that she agrees with the boy's confession.

data.故事: 小杨所在的公司周三有周例会。某周一，领导带着小王去会见客户张局，两人一直相谈甚欢，但谈的都是一些无关痛痒的话题，因为正事存在观点分歧。眼看着将近饭点，出现了下面几句对话： 领导：“张局，快到饭点了，看您有时间吗？想约您吃个饭？” 然后领导转过身，边眨眼睛，边对小杨说：“小杨，咱们晚上单位还有会议吗？”
data.问题: 当领导问小杨这个问题的时候，他的目的是什么？
data.选项A: A. 领导想向小杨询问会议时间，以安排和客户的饭局。
data.选项B: B. 领导希望小杨回答今晚有会议，以此借口结束会面。
data.选项C: C.领导想了解小杨对周例会的准备情况。
data.选项D: D. 领导希望询问小杨愿不愿不参加会议，而陪他们吃饭。
data.STORY: Xiao Yang's company holds a weekly meeting every Wednesday. On a certain Monday, the leader takes Xiao Wang to meet with client Director Zhang. The two of them chat happily, but they only talk about some irrelevant topics because there are disagreements on the main issues. As it approaches mealtime, the following conversation occurs: Leader: "Director Zhang, it is almost mealtime, do you have time? I want to invite you to have a meal." Then the leader turns around, winks, and says to Xiao Yang: "Xiao Yang, do we have a meeting at the unit tonight?"
data.QUESTION: What is the leader's purpose when he asks Xiao Yang this question?
data.OPTION-A: The leader wants to ask Xiao Yang about the meeting time to arrange a meal with the client.
data.OPTION-B: The leader hopes Xiao Yang answers that there is a meeting tonight, so he can use this as an excuse to end the meeting.
data.OPTION-C: The leader wants to understand Xiao Yang's preparation for the weekly meeting.
data.OPTION-D: The leader wants to ask if Xiao Yang is willing to skip the meeting and join them for dinner.

小领导在向小杨询问今晚有会议还是没有会议时，进行了眨眼的动作。这样的行为常常表示意味。根据故事内容接下来的事件“因为正分歧，领导婉言谢绝了午餐邀约”，表明在这个问题上，领导的“意味”应该与继续会议与终止会面的这个比对之中有关。

[步骤2]
领导已经婉言谢绝了客户的午餐邀请。但这个问题似乎也是一种婉言谢绝，但不是因为正事不能商量，紧急情况等，而似乎可以让小王继续待在会场，重要的是这个问题应该向能够理解身为小王的角色中的人发问。 roadmap arrows

[步骤3]
所以一步一步地分析后，我们可以可以认为，领导提这款问题是因为另一个“意味”，也就是真相在于领导想让客户等在这，试图通过提问，小杨意其中加pressure讓客户等在那。

data.故事: 某天小明路过一条小巷，巷口有家小摊在卖炒货。因为小明很喜欢吃瓜子，就上前购买了两斤，在购买时小明递给老板一张百元大钞，老板接过钱，低头和老板娘嘀咕几句，又把前一张钞票递了出来，说：“找不开，没零钱。”小明感到有些奇怪，但也没多想，接过钱正想走开，旁边路过的张三自言自语般地说了一句“你这瓜子，不像真货啊。” 说完张三就走了，老板只勾着头不吭声。
data.问题: 当张三说这句话的时候，他真正想说的是什么？

data.选项C: C.张三在讽刺小明喜欢吃的瓜子品种质量较差。
data.选项D: D.张三在表示看不起小明购买瓜子这种行为。
data.STORY: One day, Xiao Ming passes by a small alley, there is a small stall at the entrance of the alley that sells fried goods. Because Xiao Ming likes to eat melon seeds very much, he steps forward to buy two pounds. When buying, Xiao Ming gives the boss a hundred yuan bill, the boss takes the money, lowers his head and mutters a few words with the boss lady, and then hands out the previous bill, saying, "I can't make change, no small change." Xiao Ming feels a bit strange, but doesn't think much about it, takes the money and is about to walk away, Zhang San, who is passing by, says to himself, "Your melon seeds, they don't look like the real thing." After saying this, Zhang San walks away, and the boss just lowers his head and says nothing.
data.QUESTION: What does Zhang San really want to say when he says this?
data.OPTION-A: Zhang San is hinting that the boss changes Xiao Ming's real money into counterfeit money.
data.OPTION-B: Zhang San is reminding Xiao Ming that this small stall may be selling fake melon seeds.
data.OPTION-C: Zhang San is mocking that the quality of the melon seeds Xiao Ming likes to eat is poor.
data.OPTION-D: Zhang San is expressing his disdain for Xiao Ming's behavior of buying melon seeds.

data.选项C: C. 小王暗示这个人应当把丢在地上的烟头捡起来。

data.QUESTION: What does Xiao Wang really mean when he says this?

data.OPTION-B: Xiao Wang asks this person if the cigarette butt belongs to him.

data.OPTION-D: Xiao Wang notices this person's smoking habit.

[推理]
我们可以从以下几点来进行推理：

1. 弄烟头丢地并不意味着一定是烟头属于丢掉的个人。
   必须注意到，其实烟头是除这人之外的任何人也可能丢的。

2. 我们忽略了“疑似来自此人”指的可能的 errorMsg 是他丢东西并不一定烟头属于他。但未表明正确答案是表达遗失了东西。

3. 如果服务生小王说这句话时，真正想说的意思只是提醒这个人遗失了物品，那么提醒这人 “您掉了”，也可以。因此，这样说感觉冒昧。

4. 我们考虑到了抽烟的习惯，这在问题一中并不相关。

5. 综合分析之后，最合理的解释是服务生小王注意到了这个人抽烟的习惯。没有更合理的解释。

所以答案是D.

data.故事: 19世纪，在奥地利的维也纳，妇女们喜欢戴一种高高耸起的帽子。她们进剧场看戏也不愿将帽子摘下，以致后排的观众被挡住了视线。经理上台请在座的女观众将帽子摘下来，然而说了半天妇女们也不予以理睬。最后经理又补充了一句：“那么，这样吧，年纪大一点的女士可以照顾，不必脱帽。”
data.问题: 剧场经理说这些话时，他真正想说的意思是什么？
data.选项A: A. 他希望所有的女士都将帽子摘下来。

data.选项C: C. 他对戴帽子的女士感到恼火。
data.选项D: D. 他在夸赞年纪大的女士的优雅。
data.STORY: In the 19th century, in Vienna, Austria, women like to wear a kind of towering hat. They go to the theater to watch plays and do not want to take off their hats, so the audience in the back row is blocked. The manager goes on stage to ask the female audience to take off their hats, but the women ignore him after a long talk. Finally, the manager adds one more sentence: "So, like this, older ladies can take care, no need to take off the hat."
data.QUESTION: When the theater manager says these words, what does he really want to say?
data.OPTION-A: He hopes all ladies take off their hats.
data.OPTION-B: He only hopes young ladies take off their hats.
data.OPTION-C: He is annoyed with the ladies wearing hats.
data.OPTION-D: He is praising the elegance of older ladies.

data.OPTION-C: Teacher Zhao implies that all students should focus their attention on the class.
data.OPTION-D: Teacher Zhao hopes that the students can understand the hard work of teaching.

data.故事: 欧阳是个高中生，他的坐位在班上的最后一排。一天，他的老师陈老师在课上问他：“欧阳，窗外的风景怎么样呢？”

data.STORY: Ouyang is a high school student, his seat is in the last row of the class. One day, his teacher, Mr. Chen, asks him in class, "Ouyang, how is the scenery outside the window?"

data.OPTION-A: Mr. Chen worries that Ouyang, sitting in the last row, may not see the blackboard clearly.

data.OPTION-D: Mr. Chen hopes that Ouyang appreciates the scenery outside the window, feeling the beauty of nature.

data.故事:

他很耿直的问工作人员：“我朋友在外地，我可以代签吗？”
工作人员说：“这里有监控，是没法别人代签的，出去找本人签。”
他很着急的说：“我朋友真的回不来，行个方便吧。”
工作人员还是那句话：“这里有监控，别人没法代签，出去找本人签。”

data.选项C: C. 工作人员是再次确认了规定，即银行内不允许他人代签。
data.选项D: D. 工作人员是在建议鸿杰去找合适的签字工具。
data.STORY:
Hongjie goes to the bank to help a friend with some business. His friend is out of town. He gets the form that needs to be filled out from the staff and stops when he sees the signature column because it requires the person's own signature.
He asks the staff very straightforwardly: "My friend is out of town, can I sign for him?"
The staff says: "There is surveillance here, it is impossible for others to sign on behalf, go find the person to sign."
He says anxiously: "My friend really can't come back, please make it convenient."
The staff still says: "There is surveillance here, others can't sign on behalf, go find the person to sign."

data.OPTION-C: The staff is reconfirming the rule that the bank does not allow others to sign on behalf.
data.OPTION-D: The staff is suggesting that Hongjie find a suitable signing tool.

The two of them chat happily, but they only talk about some irrelevant topics because there are disagreements on the main issues. As it approaches mealtime, the following conversation occurs: Leader: "Director Zhang, it is almost mealtime, do you have time? I want to invite you to have a meal." Then the leader turns around, winks, and says to Xiao Yang: "Xiao Yang, do we have a meeting at the unit tonight?"
data.QUESTION: What is the leader's purpose when he asks Xiao Yang this question?
data.OPTION-A: The leader wants to ask Xiao Yang about the meeting time to arrange a meal with the client.
data.OPTION-B: The leader hopes Xiao Yang answers that there is a meeting tonight, so he can use this as an excuse to end the meeting.
data.OPTION-C: The leader wants to understand Xiao Yang's preparation for the weekly meeting.
data.OPTION-D: The leader wants to ask if Xiao Yang is willing to skip the meeting and join them for dinner.

data.故事: 小汪和网络上认识的女生小兰的见面约在了酒店。在前台，小兰不愿意出示身份证登记。 前台工作人员问：“您是一位还是两位？两位的话需要出示双方身份证的先生。” 小汪回头看着小兰，她慢慢走到沙发边上坐下仍然没有出示身份证的意思。于是小汪转过头问：“两位，那怎么办？” 此时前台工作人员又问：“您是一位入住还是两位呢？”
data.问题: 当工作人员提出这个问题的时候，他的目的是什么？
data.选项A: A. 他没有听清楚小汪之前的回答，要再进行确认。
data.选项B: B. 他正在重新核实小汪的住宿需求。
data.选项C: C. 他暗示小汪可回答一位入住，这样只需要用一个人的身份证。
data.选项D: D. 他暗示不出示两人身份证就不可以一起住宿。
data.STORY: Xiao Wang and the girl he meets online, Xiao Lan, arrange to meet at a hotel. At the front desk, Xiao Lan does not want to show her ID for registration. The front desk staff asks, "Are you one or two? If two, the gentleman needs to show both IDs." Xiao Wang turns his head and looks at Xiao Lan, she slowly walks to the edge of the sofa and sits down, still showing no intention of showing her ID. So Xiao Wang turns his head and asks, "Two, what to do?" At this time, the front desk staff asks again, "Are you checking in for one or two?"
data.QUESTION: What is his purpose when the staff asks this question?
data.OPTION-A: He does not hear Xiao Wang's previous answer clearly and needs to confirm again.
data.OPTION-B: He is re-verifying Xiao Wang's accommodation needs.
data.OPTION-C: He hints that Xiao Wang can answer one person checks in, so only one person's ID is needed.
data.OPTION-D: He hints that if they do not show both IDs, they cannot stay together.
